name: PGA116 Luxury 4BR at PGA West!
description: Property Description:This is a luxury PGA West home located behind guarded, private gates on the 12th green of the famous Nicklaus Tournament course. This spectacular 3,450 square foot home features 14-foot ceilings, private pool and heated spa.Every bedroom has its own bathroom and TV. One of the bedrooms is a private casita for that couple that wishes more privacy. All beds in the home are either King or Queen size and a new 56 inch 4K television in the family room.The elegant gourmet kitchen is equipped for the most demanding chef plus granite countertops, walk-in pantry, built-in ovens, refrigerator, dishwasher, the finest of cookware and a separate laundry room with washer and dryer. The great room with wet bar, features a large screen High Definition Television and numerous DVDs for your viewing pleasure.Overlooking the lush 12th green of Nicklaus golf course, the backyard patio with built-in barbecue features extensive lounge chairs, outside music, and misters for your cooling pleasure. Patio seating can accommodate 10 people.The large master, with its high ceiling, is elegantly decorated with a view of the pool and 12th green. The spacious master bath features an enormous walk-in closet. Other amenities includes high speed internet, music throughout the home, private courtyard and private casita .

name: PGA117 Elegant PGA West estate!
description: Property Description:A spectacular estate located in the private PGA West community, overlooking sweeping panoramic views of the 16th fairway on the Jack Nicklaus Tournament Course.Situated on a lake with multiple mountain views, this home is an entertainers delight with inviting saltwater pool and spa, and two expansive covered patios with two areas to dine outdoors. Each bedroom is a suite making this property the ideal choice for families or friends who enjoy their private space. Outdoors: This spacious and inviting yard is the perfect setting to entertain friends and family with gorgeous golf course views of the 16th fairway. Majestic mountain views in every direction, and the privacy to enjoy it all while being slightly elevated off the course provides an outstanding place for family enjoyment. The beautiful saltwater pool and spa with tranquil spillover water feature are the centerpiece to the entertaining space, which also features 5 lounge chairs, and a covered patio with outdoor dining for 4 and BBQ. Spend your days in the backyard around the pool, and your nights in the intimate courtyard with a second dining space for 4, and an outdoor seating area with sofa and two chairs. The courtyard is the perfect outdoor lounging area for quiet time to curl up with a great book, or with your morning cup of coffee. Indoors: The upgrades are all here in the gourmet kitchen including a 5 burner gas stove, double ovens, fridge, dishwasher, slab granite and rich custom cabinetry. The oversized center island is at the heart of this kitchen, with raised bar seating for 6. The dining space is just off the kitchen with seating for 6-8 and gorgeous views of the golf course. Just off the dining space is a wet bar with wine fridge and bar seating for 2. The living room is open to the kitchen for entertaining purposes and features a sofa, two comfy chairs, gas fireplace, and HDTV. The spacious courtyard and backyard connect when the wall of sliding glass doors open on each side of the living room creating a great breezeway and an open space for entertaining. Bedroom Descriptions: The luxurious and spacious master retreat features a Cal King bed, a plush chaise lounge that converts to a twin, HDTV, desk and a sliding glass door for a private entrance to the patio and pool area. The large en-suite master bathroom has his and hers sinks and vanities, a dreamy jacuzzi soaking tub, and a large tiled shower. The master suite closet is a large walk-in with enough room for all of your vacation clothes, as well as storing 3 twin rollaway beds for additional sleeping accommodations. Suite 2 features a Cal King bed, reach-in closet, HDTV, and en-suite bathroom featuring a sink, and a large tiled shower. Suite 2 also features a Twin sleeper sofa. Suite 3 features a Queen bed, reach-in closet, HDTV, and a private en-suite bath with sink and tub/shower. Suite 3 also has a sliding glass door that leads to the front courtyard. Suite 4 is located in the detached casita that can be accessed through the front courtyard of the home. The casita features a Queen bed, kitchenette with sink, mini fridge and coffee maker, a walk-in closet, and a twin bed with twin trundle underneath with HDTV. The casita also has a private bathroom with sink and shower. Bed and Sleeping Summary: 2 Cal Kings, 2 Queens, 5 Twins, 2 Twin Sleeper Sofas. Sleeps 12.

name: Snow Flower, Park City #80
description: Property Description:1 Bedroom (loft), 2 Bathrooms, Sleeps 4, Ski in/outLocation! Location! Location! This is a slope side condo at the base of Park City Mountain. This condo is located next to the Three Kings, First Time, and Eagle chairlifts.This upgraded studio/loft (bedroom) condo is located on the top floor of beautiful Snowflower resort. It has 2 full bathrooms and sleeping arrangements for 4. The downstairs bathroom has a unique spa tub. This condo has cathedral ceilings and a large balcony with beautiful views of the slopes at Park City. The condo was recently upgraded with granite countertops and stainless steel appliances. There is a Cal King bed and bathroom on the loft with a sleeper sofa in the downstairs family room. The resort also has a large slope side pool kept at a constant 102 degrees where you can watch the skiers/boarders while relaxing.In addition to being on the slopes, this home is a short distance to the shopping/night life in old town. Or if you just can't get enough of the mountain, there is night skiing just outside your door as well. There are 2 other ski resorts within a 5 minute drive. The Canyons resort and world famous Deer Valley are very easy to drive to. When you are done on the mountain, the resort center is a 2 minute walk. At the resort center you can ice skate, dine, or wind down at one of the bars. Everything you need in Park City is an easy walk or short drive away. You will be making first tracks each day from this slope side condominium. Ski run views while relaxing on the private deck is just one of the perks this property offers. Onsite amenities include multiple swimming pools, hot tubs, tennis courts, underground parking, exercise facilities and more!
